cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it studies the evolution of the network of norms that sustain the online Wikipedia community. It also touches upon topics related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it analyzes the interpersonal interactions governed by the norms. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it explores the social norms of an online community, cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it discusses the evolution of a system of norms, and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) as it studies the social network of Wikipedia's normative evolution.
